<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-21T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-21T19:00:00-05:00" n="454" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/5860: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-21T19:00:00-05:00">February 21, 1934—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>49. Your 93, February 20, 11 a.m.—Hukuang loan.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>You are authorized to sign the joint memorandum.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Department would suggest, however, if your colleagues consent,
                                that the word “validity”, the seventh word from the end of the third
                                paragraph of the proposed joint memorandum, be changed to “value”,
                                and that there be added to the last paragraph of the proposed
                                memorandum the words “and previous memoranda and notes,” if in fact
                                there were previous memoranda and notes on the subject.<note n="2" xml:id="d454fn2">The text of the joint memorandum, dated March
                                    7, 1934, contained these changes, except that the two words “and
                                    notes” were omitted (893.51/5876).</note></item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>